Commentary Text: Akash Madhwal to Stoinis, SIX, Stoinis finishes on a high. And has Tim David done some damage to himself as he went for the catch at long-off. He is lying flat on his back surrounded by a few MI mates. David seems to have landed awkwardly on his back and jammed his head on to the turf. Coming back to the ball: It was full on the stumps, Stoinis makes room and lofts, one hand comes off and David on the leap over his head, stretching gets a right hand to it, but it goes over. Full marks to the effort but it is LSG and Stoinis who end big

Commentary Text: Chawla to de Kock, out Caught by Ishan Kishan!! Again Chawla takes a wicket first ball of his spell. Nonchalant from Ishan Kishan and Rohit comically is having a go at Ishan to stump de Kock as the batter was out of his crease and started to walk off. Ishan again with nonchalance tells Rohit that there is a review so why bother. Superbly bowled googly to start with, tossed up outside off, de Kock gets forward to drive and a healthy nick and well caught by Ishan who did not even appeal for the catch for he was so sure. Rohit on the other hand is tensed. de Kock walks off for he knew he had edged it. de Kock c Ishan Kishan b Chawla 16(15) [6s-2]

Commentary Text: Behrendorff to Prerak Mankad, out Caught by Ishan Kishan!! Gone first ball. Nothing shot and Prerak Mankad goes for a golden duck. Behrendorff punches the air in delight. Commentary Text: Ravi Bishnoi to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Naveen-ul-Haq!! Huge wicket! A sigh of relief for them as Kishan was going all guns blazing! Was the googly and Ishan Kishan rocked back in the crease to smoke it over deep mid-wicket. Miscues it altogether as he gets a top edge and Naveen stationed near the boundary keeps his cool and completes a pretty safe catch. Commentary Text: Yash Thakur to Rohit, SIX, unlucky for LSG. Had Bishnoi stayed deep that would have been an easier opportunity. It was short and slanted into the body, Rohit pulls and it goes flat to the left of fine leg where Bishnoi overran and ended up making a meal of the catch. While trying to backpedal at the end, he lost balance and fell on the boundary cushions before throwing the ball back into play. Just a matter of few inches, matter of few seconds - but Mumbai are not complaining though, it's a third maximum for the MI skipper
